(336, 'Meeting with founders at GFF sidelines 2024-08-29T18:28:00.000+05:30: Attendees: @Anonymous and @Rahul Mathur 1. Avi 1. Darbangha 1. IIT-D for college ; electrical engineering 1. Wanted to do PhD 1. Joined Booz out of college 1. 2013 → 1st company; e-comm boom 1. 2015 got acquired by CarDekho for PriceDekho 1. COS → 8 to 9 month stint 1. Built auto lending business at CarDekho → worked with a bunch of banks 1. Good understanding of FinOps 1. Credence → 2nd company 1. 2017 → 2023 1. Initially only domestic lending 1. Then COVID hit → so began lending to study abroad market 1. NBFC license got returned due to Mauritius money 1. 2nd buyout offer from Shriram Finance 1. Lending book was subsumed into Travel India 1. Top 3 learnings → asked by @Anonymous 1. Find problem statements which let you work on them for 10-15 years 1. Arbitrage opportunities exist for a reason; focus on fundamental problems 1. Other co-fo 1. From J&K → Studied there till 10th standard 1. BTech Delhi 1. Interest in cyber & data security 1. Joined IIIT Delhi as a Privacy Researcher 1. Masters in Data Security from France 1. Learned about GDPR 1. 1st company 1. Disecto 1. Got Govt grants 1. Homomorphic encryption for data sharing 1. Blume & Omidyar keen to invest 1. Spent 2 years 1. India’s top law firm 1. Built their privacy vertical 1. Didn’t enjoy doing consulting 1. How do Co-Fo’s know each other? 1. Met online on LinkedIn 1. Privacy focus was of interest to both 1. Why this? 1. Younger generation cares 1...'),
