(355, 'Note from @Anonymous 2025-10-14: Sharing the note for our $50K investment in Potpie as part of their seed round of $2M a $12.5M valuation cap, led by Emergent VC - $1.5M. About the Company Potpie is building an AI-driven behavioural code auditor that enables developers to ship bug-free code to production confidently by automatically validating the intended code behaviour at every git push. Problem Statement: engineers today spend nearly 5x the time testing vs writing code, with ~40% of total developer bandwidth going into writing and maintaining test cases. Despite this, $2.4T in losses were attributed to poor-quality software shipped in the US in 2022. Momentum’s product uses code behaviour analysis, test generation, and automated validation to ensure code correctness in real-time. Core Product Features: - Behavioural code auditor that analyzes code functionality, efficacy, and inter-compatibility. - Automatically generates end-to-end tests and integrates them into the repo. - Visualizes codebase architecture to catch dependency issues. - Ensures every commit meets defined behavioural criteria before production deployment. Traction & Progress - Open-source v1 launched (FY25 Q1). - 15+ pilots landed in the past 8 weeks with companies like Tata 1mg and Bain & Co. - 2 pilots completed, 2 ongoing, and 15 in pipeline. - Product roadmap includes enterprise rollout with self-healing tests, debugging in natural language, SOC2/GDPR compliance, and CI/CD integrations. Founders [Aditi ...'),
(356, 'About the Company: PowerEdge provides a suite of bank-tech solutions focused on: 1. **Collections Management**: - Currently managing ~40,000 customers with 90-93% recovery rates in early buckets. - Their collections stack combines digital, telephony, and field channels and has 30% lower losses than industry average. - Collection revenue is projected to contribute ~$21M by FY27. 1. **CCMS Middleware**: - Building modular tools over legacy CCMS platforms (VisionPlus, TSYS) to enable better reward programs and customer experience without banks having to switch cores. - Revenue model: ₹5/card/month; already integrated with Yes Bank, BoB Cards. 1. **Fraud Ring Detection**: - Uses graph algorithms and ML on application data to detect fraud. - 60% precision with 1–2% match rate vs Hunter’s 3% precision on 10% match rate. - Live with Uni, in PoC with Navi, Jupiter. Current Revenue**:** - $1.1M booked, projected to hit $4.5M ARR by March 2025 ~85% of current revenue from Uni - Clients: Uni, Fibe, OneCard, MoneyView - PoCs in progress with Navi, Jupiter - Banks live: BoB, Yes Bank (through Uni relationships) Founders **Abhishek Gupta (CEO)** - Ex-CTO @ Uni, LazyPay/PayU - Deep tech experience in credit infra, strong founder-market fit for bank-tech infra. - IIT Kanpur, M.Tech CS **Ajay Jadaun (COO)** - Ex-Sr. Director of Risk @ Uni, Head of Cards Risk @ Bajaj - Equifax, StanC alumni - IIT Madras Chem Eng ’10 - Strong risk ops mind with understanding of cards and collections **Apoorv Ag...'),
(357, 'Deck 2025-02-11T20:15:00.000+05:30: Based on the PowerUp Money pitch deck, here are the key points: **Company Overview:** - Building a DIY mutual fund advisory platform targeting the mass affluent segment with portfolios between 5L-1Cr - Offers fund selection, portfolio review, and rebalancing through an app-based product - Currently has 155,619 users acquired at <$1 CAC **Business Model:** - Freemium model with Elite subscription at ₹999/year - 53% of surveyed users willing to pay for subscription - Claims to deliver similar alpha as traditional advisors at 1/300th the cost **Traction & Growth:** - YouTube channel with 67K subscribers and 10M+ views in 6 months - Planning to expand into FDs and other wealth products - Raising $5M to reach $14M ARR by April 2027 **Team:** - Led by Prateek Jindal (ex-Uni Cards CPO, ex-Ola Financial Services) - Key hires from Uni, Groww, UpGrad with experience in design, engineering, and marketing **Market Opportunity:** - Targeting growing mutual fund market (52M investors in 2024 → projected 116M by 2029) - 83-88% of users face challenges in fund selection, review, and rebalancing
Notes from Taha 2025-02-12T14:03:00.000+05:30: **RA** Spiky – 0.5; not in the same league as our wealth EFs; can potentially be a good FF but not as spiky as Saurabh @ Stable. Positives – - Good product guy - Interesting value prop - Nitin views - Top tier cap table coming together - Probably top quartile of founders that I’ve seen at DeVC - Some unfair advantage if...'),
(358, 'Discussion 2026-01-09T10:24:00.000+05:30: 1. Cash was his wing mate in IITB 1. Has iterated on 6 ideas - didn’t start on any 1. Rajat believes that this will be a last round & go to Avi directly 1. Could be a Chirag like situation ---
Rahul - 2026-01-18: Avi has met, Z47 has passed due to earlier context')
